# Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

A11y non-negotiable. Her PR'da manuel check + axe-core otomatik test. Eksik a11y = blocked merge.

**Kontrast ve renk:** Mümkün olduğunca `docs/lean-design-system/tokens.css` içindeki foreground/background çiftleri; rastgele hex ile design system’i bypass etme (`26-lean-design-system.mdc`).

## 4 Temel İlke (POUR)

1. **Perceivable** — içerik tüm duyularla algılanabilir
2. **Operable** — UI tüm input metodlarıyla kullanılabilir
3. **Understandable** — içerik + UI anlamlı
4. **Robust** — çeşitli assistive tech'lerde çalışır

## Semantic HTML

Div/span değil doğru element:

```typescript
// ✗ Yanlış
<div onClick={handleSubmit}>Kaydet</div>

// ✓ Doğru
<button onClick={handleSubmit} type="button">Kaydet</button>

// ✗ Yanlış
<div className="nav">
  <div onClick={...}>Ana Sayfa</div>
</div>

// ✓ Doğru
<nav>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/">Ana Sayfa</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>
```

Landmark element'ler her sayfada:
- `<header>` — site header
- `<nav>` — navigation
- `<main>` — primary content
- `<aside>` — sidebar
- `<footer>` — site footer

## Form Accessibility

shadcn `<FormField>` zaten doğru ARIA wire eder. İki şart:
1. `<FormLabel>` her field için
2. `<FormMessage />` error region

```typescript
<FormField
  control={form.control}
  name="email"
  render={({ field }) => (
    <FormItem>
      <FormLabel>E-posta *</FormLabel>
      <FormControl>
        <Input 
          {...field} 
          type="email" 
          autoComplete="email"
          aria-required="true"
        />
      </FormControl>
      <FormMessage />
    </FormItem>
  )}
/>
```

Otomatik yapılan:
- `aria-describedby` → `<FormMessage>` ID'sine
- `aria-invalid` → error varsa `true`
- `htmlFor` label'dan input'a

Required field:
- Label'da `*` visual işaret
- `aria-required="true"` programmatic
- Zod `min(1)` backend + frontend validation

## Keyboard Navigation

Her interaktif element klavye ile erişilebilir:

- **Tab / Shift+Tab** — sonraki / önceki focusable
- **Enter / Space** — button activation
- **Escape** — modal/dialog kapat
- **Arrow keys** — menu item / tab / combobox navigation
- **Home / End** — liste başı / sonu

Custom component'larda keyboard event handle:

```typescript
<div 
  role="button"
  tabIndex={0}
  onClick={handleClick}
  onKeyDown={(e) => {
    if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
      e.preventDefault();
      handleClick();
    }
  }}
>
  Custom Button
</div>
```

Mümkünse `<button>` kullan — tüm keyboard behavior built-in.

### Skip Link

Sayfa başında "Ana içeriğe atla" link:

```typescript
// app/layout.tsx
<a 
  href="#main-content" 
  className="sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:fixed focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:bg-primary focus:text-primary-foreground focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:rounded"
>
  Ana içeriğe atla
</a>
// ...
<main id="main-content">...</main>
```

## Focus Management

### Focus Visible

Tüm interaktif element'lerde visible focus ring:

```css
/* globals.css */
:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--ring);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

Tailwind zaten focus styles getirir:
```typescript
<Button className="focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
```

### Focus Trap (Modal)

shadcn `<Dialog>` focus trap built-in — sadece kullan, manuel implement etme.

### Focus After Action

- Submit fail → ilk error field'a focus (RHF otomatik)
- Modal açılıyor → ilk focusable'a
- Modal kapanıyor → tetikleyici button'a geri dön
- Action → sonuç element'ine (toast, yeni content)

```typescript
const triggerRef = useRef<HTMLButtonElement>(null);

<Dialog onOpenChange={(open) => {
  if (!open) triggerRef.current?.focus();
}}>
  <DialogTrigger ref={triggerRef}>Aç</DialogTrigger>
  ...
</Dialog>
```

## ARIA — Sparingly, Correctly

ARIA sadece semantic HTML yetersiz olduğunda:

```typescript
// Good: complex component
<div role="alert" aria-live="polite">
  {error && <p>{error}</p>}
</div>

// Bad: unnecessary
<button role="button">Kaydet</button>  // button already has role
```

### Landmarks

```typescript
<main role="main">...</main>        // genellikle gereksiz
<nav aria-label="Main">...</nav>   // birden fazla nav varsa ayrıştır
```

### Labeling

```typescript
// Icon-only button
<Button aria-label="Kullanıcıyı sil">
  <Trash2 className="h-4 w-4" />
</Button>

// Labeled by another element
<div>
  <h2 id="dialog-title">Sil</h2>
  <Dialog aria-labelledby="dialog-title">...</Dialog>
</div>

// Described by
<Input 
  aria-describedby="password-hint"
/>
<p id="password-hint">En az 12 karakter, 1 özel karakter içermeli</p>
```

### Live Regions

Dynamic content changes:

```typescript
// Toast — auto-announced to screen readers
import { toast } from 'sonner';
toast.success('Kaydedildi');  // sonner uses aria-live

// Custom live region
<div role="status" aria-live="polite">
  {count} sonuç bulundu
</div>

<div role="alert" aria-live="assertive">
  {criticalError}
</div>
```

`polite` — user'ın dikkatini bekler; `assertive` — anında duyurur (kritik).

## Color Contrast

WCAG AA:
- **Normal text** (< 18pt): ≥ 4.5:1
- **Large text** (≥ 18pt or 14pt bold): ≥ 3:1
- **Non-text UI** (icons, borders): ≥ 3:1

Tailwind default colors çoğunlukla uyumlu ama custom color eklerken check:
- https://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/
- Storybook a11y addon

Color-only information yasak:

```typescript
// ✗ Sadece renk farkı
<span className="text-red-500">Aktif değil</span>

// ✓ Icon + renk + text
<span className="text-red-600 flex items-center gap-1">
  <XCircle className="h-3 w-3" /> Aktif değil
</span>
```

Screen reader only text — Tailwind `sr-only`:
```typescript
<Button size="icon">
  <span className="sr-only">Kullanıcıyı düzenle</span>
  <Pencil className="h-4 w-4" />
</Button>
```

## Keyboard-Only User Testing

Her feature için:
1. `Tab` ile her interactive element'e eriş
2. `Enter/Space` ile trigger et
3. `Esc` ile modal kapat
4. Focus order mantıklı (DOM order)
5. Keyboard trap yok (focus çıkabilir)

## Screen Reader Testing

- **macOS**: VoiceOver (Cmd+F5)
- **Windows**: NVDA (free)
- **Chrome**: ChromeVox extension

Test prompt'u:
- Sayfa yüklenince ne anonslanıyor?
- Button'a focus olunca amaç anlaşılıyor mu?
- Form error'u duyuruluyor mu?
- Dynamic content (toast, modal) announce oluyor mu?

## Skeleton + Loading States

Screen reader loading bilmeli:

```typescript
<div role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-busy={isLoading}>
  {isLoading ? (
    <>
      <span className="sr-only">Yükleniyor...</span>
      <UserListSkeleton />
    </>
  ) : (
    <UserList data={data} />
  )}
</div>
```

## axe-core Integration

Test'lerde otomatik a11y check:

```typescript
// tests/a11y.spec.ts
import { render } from '@testing-library/react';
import { axe, toHaveNoViolations } from 'jest-axe';

expect.extend(toHaveNoViolations);

test('UserForm has no accessibility violations', async () => {
  const { container } = render(<UserForm />);
  const results = await axe(container);
  expect(results).toHaveNoViolations();
});
```

## Translations (Language)

Root layout `lang="tr"`:

```typescript
<html lang="tr">
```

Parça başka dildeyse işaretle:
```typescript
<p lang="en">Hello world</p>
```

## Reduced Motion

Kullanıcı reduced motion tercih ettiyse animation'ları kaldır:

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  * {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

Tailwind `motion-safe:` + `motion-reduce:` variants ile:
```typescript
<div className="motion-safe:animate-spin motion-reduce:hidden">
```

## Banned Patterns

- `<div onClick={...}>` interactive (use `<button>`)
- `tabIndex="-1"` make focusable that wasn't (only for skip)
- `aria-label` duplicates visible text (screen reader reads twice)
- `role="button"` on a `<button>` (redundant)
- Image without `alt` (decorative → `alt=""`, meaningful → descriptive)
- Icon-only button without `aria-label` or `sr-only` text
- Color as only differentiator (pattern + icon + text)
- Autoplay media (WCAG fail)
- Keyboard trap — user must be able to escape focus
- Positive `tabIndex` values (disrupts natural order)

